# TypeScript
- `strict` mode; no `any` (use `unknown` + narrowing). Explicit param and return types on exported functions.
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes. Avoid TS `enum` — use `const` object + union type. (Postgres enums are separate.)
- Default export only for Next.js pages/layouts; named exports elsewhere.
- Derive types from source of truth: use generated `src/types/database.ts` for DB rows and Zod `z.infer` for validated input.
- Early returns for error conditions; no deep nesting.
